definition.value: A (2R)-2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-mercaptolactic acid, obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 7-methyloctanoic acid.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate groups of 7-methyloctanoyl-CoA. Major species at pH 7.3.
A tripeptide consisting of L-glutamic acid, glycine and L-phenylalanine residues joined in sequence.
An  organosulfinate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the sulfinic acid group of hypotaurine.
A tripeptide composed of L-lysine, L-tyrosine and L-glutamic acid joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of L-methionine, L-alanine, and L-methionine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A D-5-monosubstituted hydantoin that is  imidazolidine-2,4-dione in which the pro-R hydrogen at position 5 has been replaced by a phenyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of N-carbamoyl-D-phenylglycine. The major microspecies species at pH 7.3.
